<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<task id="usermanagement-EditUser">
    <title>Edit User Profile</title>
    <taskbody>
        <prereq>
           <ul>
            <li>You must have the SECURITY_ADMIN role.</li>
            <li>To check currently assigned role(s), select the User ID on the top right hand corner
           and click <b>View User Profile</b> from the drop-down list. Assigned roles are displayed.
           </li>
           </ul>
        </prereq>
        <context>
           <p>
                <b>Objective</b>
            </p>
           <p>This tutorial describes the steps to edit an ENM user.
           The <b>Edit User</b> allows to update the user details, and, with the buttons in the action bar, to <b>Change User Local Password</b>, <b>Duplicate</b>, <b>Delete</b>, <b>Terminate Sessions</b>, <b>Revoke Force Password Change</b>. For the description of these actions, see the associated User Interface pages.
            </p>

            <p>
                <b>Outline</b>
            </p>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <xref href="#1">Click Edit Profile</xref>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <xref href="#2">Enter User Details</xref>
               </li>
               <li><xref href="#3">Create New Role (optional)</xref>
               </li>
               <li>
                    <xref href="#4">Assign Required Role(s)</xref>
               </li>
               <li>
                    <xref href="#5">Create a New Target Group (optional)</xref>
               </li>
               <li>
                    <xref href="#6">Assign required Target Group(s) (optional)</xref>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <xref href="#7">Click Save</xref>
               </li>
            </ol>
        </context>
       <steps>
            <step id="1">
                <cmd>Click Edit Profile</cmd>
                <info>
                   <ol>
                     <li>Launch <xref scope="external" href="/#usermanagement">
                            User Management.</xref></li>
                     <li>Select a user from the <b>Users Profiles</b> table.</li>
                     <li>Click <b>Edit Profile</b>. The <b>Edit User Profile</b> page is displayed.</li>
                  </ol>
                </info>
           </step>
           <step id="2">
                <cmd>Enter User Details</cmd>
                <info>
                        <p>Enter required <b>General Information</b>.</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Name</b>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Surname</b>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Email Address</b>
                                    (optional)
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Status</b>
                                    (optional and disabled by default)
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Description</b>
                                    (optional)
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Authentication Mode</b>
                                    (Local by default)
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <b>Password Ageing</b>
                                    (select required password aging) <xref href="#help/app/userprofile/ui~PAW" type="concept" scope="external">(More information)</xref>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                    <p>For more information on editing a User Profile, see the  <i>
                        <xref href="../ui.xml#edituser">Edit User</xref></i>.
                    </p>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="3">
                <cmd>Create New Role (optional)</cmd>
                <info>
                    <p>If the required role to be added to the user is not displayed in the <b>Roles</b> table:
                    </p>

                    <ol>
                        <li>Click <b>Create a New Role</b>. The <b>Create User Role</b> page is displayed.
                        </li>
                        <li>To create a new role, perform the steps in <xref scope="external"
                                      href="/#help/app/rolemanagement/topic/tutorials/CreateRole~3">
                                    Create Role</xref>.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    Close the <b>Role Management</b> application if no other user roles are required.
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="4">
                <cmd>Assign Required Role(s)</cmd>
                <info>
                   <p>Click check box(es) to select the required role(s) from the <b>Roles</b> table to assign to the user.</p>
                </info>
            </step>

            <step id="5">

                <cmd>Create a New Target Group (optional)</cmd>
                <info>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Click <b>Create a New Target Group</b>. The <b>Create Target Group</b> page is displayed.
                        </li>
                        <li>To Create a new target group, perform the steps in <xref scope="external"
                                      href="/#help/app/targetmanagement/topic/tutorials/CreateTargetGroup~3"> Create Target Group</xref>.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                        Close the <b>Target Group Management</b> application if no other target groups are required.
                </info>
            </step>

            <step id="6">

                <cmd>Assign required Target Group(s) (optional)</cmd>
                <info>
                    <p>If you have to assign a target group to an ENM System Role or Custom Role</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Click <b>Service Target Groups (ALL)</b>. The <b>Assign Service Target Groups</b> flyout panel is
                            displayed.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click <b>Assign Manually</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>Select the target group from the list.</li>
                        <li>Click <b>></b> .
                        </li>
                        <li>Click <b>Apply</b>.
                        </li>
                    </ol>

                    <p>If you have to assign a target group to a COM Role or COM Role Alias:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Click <b>COM Target Groups (NONE)</b> from the <b>Target Groups Assigned</b> column in the
                            <b>Roles</b> table. The <b>Assign COM Target Groups</b> flyout panel is displayed.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click <b>Assign Manually</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>Select the target group from the list.</li>
                        <li>Click <b>></b> .
                        </li>
                        <li>Click <b>Apply</b>.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <p>If you have to assign a target group to a Task Profile Role:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Click <b>Task Profile Target Groups (NONE)</b> from the <b>Target Groups Assigned</b> column in the
                            <b>Roles</b> table. The <b>Assign Task Profile Target Groups</b> flyout panel is displayed.
                        </li>
                        <li>Click <b>Assign Manually</b>.
                        </li>
                        <li>Select the target group from the list.</li>
                        <li>Click <b>></b> .
                        </li>
                        <li>Click <b>Apply</b>.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="7">
                <cmd>Save the User Profile</cmd>
                <info>
                    Click <b>Save</b> to edit the user.
                </info>
            </step>

        </steps>
        <result>
            <p>
                The user profile is successfully updated.
            </p>
        </result>
   </taskbody>
</task>
